WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.940 --> 00:00:14.943
[dramatic music playing]

2
00:00:41.845 --> 00:00:44.347
[mysterious music playing]

3
00:00:50.437 --> 00:00:54.024
[unsettling music playing]

4
00:01:17.005 --> 00:01:19.424
[flies buzzing]

5
00:01:33.146 --> 00:01:34.231
[sighs]

6
00:01:35.065 --> 00:01:36.233
Fuck.

7
00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:41.905
[intense. ominous music playing]

8
00:01:54.918 --> 00:01:57.254
[dogs barking]

9
00:02:10.767 --> 00:02:11.768
Hey.

10
00:02:13.895 --> 00:02:15.439
I'm looking for Robert Cady.

11
00:02:16.273 --> 00:02:17.274
[sighs]

12
00:02:22.195 --> 00:02:24.573
- Am I in the right place?
- Oh. sure. ma'am. [chuckles]

13
00:02:25.323 --> 00:02:26.741
Follow me. [chuckles]

14
00:02:39.045 --> 00:02:40.380
That's him right there.

15
00:02:41.423 --> 00:02:42.424
[blows]

16
00:02:47.471 --> 00:02:48.847
Max's lady lawyer.

17
00:02:52.100 --> 00:02:56.062
Let me guess. You were
in the neighborhood and got a little lost?

18
00:02:57.522 --> 00:02:58.814
I'm looking for Crystal.

19
00:02:58.815 --> 00:03:00.484
[unsettling music playing]

20
00:03:02.611 --> 00:03:04.404
- Oh?
- Yeah.

21
00:03:09.242 --> 00:03:10.327
Are you now?

22
00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:13.121
Yeah.

23
00:03:13.705 --> 00:03:15.081
[Hester] Who's that?

24
00:03:15.749 --> 00:03:17.542
Little Anna Deveraux. Mama.

25
00:03:18.960 --> 00:03:20.795
- What's she doing here?
- Mm-hmm.

26
00:03:20.796 --> 00:03:22.588
Do they know about Crystal?

27
00:03:22.589 --> 00:03:23.757
[Robert] Now. now. now.

28
00:03:24.591 --> 00:03:26.176
Don't get your panties twisted.

29
00:03:26.802 --> 00:03:28.720
Nothing burning here but the daylight.

30
00:03:31.431 --> 00:03:32.515
Here's Crystal.

31
00:03:32.516 --> 00:03:35.893
Aw. there's my baby.

32
00:03:35.894 --> 00:03:37.394
Yeah.

33
00:03:37.395 --> 00:03:39.313
Here you go. my lovey.

34
00:03:39.314 --> 00:03:41.733
Yeah. good job.

35
00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:43.693
Mmm. Uh-huh.

36
00:03:44.194 --> 00:03:47.781
Look. if you just tell me where I can
find her. then I'll be on my way.

37
00:03:48.365 --> 00:03:49.533
You leave Crystal be.

38
00:03:51.118 --> 00:03:54.662
Took that girl half her life
to get her demons on a leash.

39
00:03:54.663 --> 00:03:57.873
I swear to God.
I will make you sorry you agitate her.

40
00:03:57.874 --> 00:03:59.668
[menacing music playing]

41
00:04:01.169 --> 00:04:02.796
You best be on your way. ma'am.

42
00:04:09.553 --> 00:04:10.554
Okay.

43
00:04:16.892 --> 00:04:19.229
It's all right.
It's all right. it's all right.

44
00:04:28.405 --> 00:04:29.990
Got nothing for you here.

45
00:04:37.456 --> 00:04:40.125
[eerie music playing]

46
00:04:52.679 --> 00:04:56.266
Just a few more things to do...

47
00:04:58.310 --> 00:05:01.396
and then I will join you.

48
00:05:10.739 --> 00:05:12.365
[intense. ominous music playing]

49
00:05:23.752 --> 00:05:26.045
["Waitin' for the Bus" playing]

50
00:05:26.046 --> 00:05:27.380
[Anna] <i>You know this girl?</i>

51
00:05:28.256 --> 00:05:30.467
- Crystal Cady.
- [bartender] Nope.

52
00:05:31.718 --> 00:05:33.344
You know the family though. right?

53
00:05:33.345 --> 00:05:35.097
They live just down the road.

54
00:05:36.932 --> 00:05:39.017
You a paying customer or not?

55
00:05:45.315 --> 00:05:48.318
Well. devil's already in the door.

56
00:05:49.569 --> 00:05:51.571
Whiskey. Make it neat. [sighs]

57
00:06:10.382 --> 00:06:11.508
[music stops]

58
00:06:22.602 --> 00:06:23.854
[inhales sharply]

59
00:06:27.399 --> 00:06:29.317
[patrons chattering]

60
00:06:46.084 --> 00:06:47.419
Hey. sunshine.

61
00:06:48.545 --> 00:06:50.504
I heard you were looking for me.

62
00:06:50.505 --> 00:06:53.091
[sinister music playing]

63
00:06:55.802 --> 00:06:57.137
Oh. fuck.

64
00:07:34.466 --> 00:07:35.592
Hello?

65
00:07:36.426 --> 00:07:37.427
Hey. bud.

66
00:07:41.056 --> 00:07:42.057
Hey.

67
00:07:43.642 --> 00:07:46.728
Uh. Zack?

68
00:07:47.813 --> 00:07:49.064
<i>Is that you?</i>

69
00:07:50.065 --> 00:07:51.066
Yeah. it's me.

70
00:07:51.691 --> 00:07:52.776
[sighs]

71
00:07:53.318 --> 00:07:54.319
[chuckles]

72
00:07:55.779 --> 00:07:56.863
Well. how you doing?

73
00:07:58.365 --> 00:07:59.366
[Zack] <i>I'm okay.</i>

74
00:08:00.242 --> 00:08:03.036
<i>How... How are you guys?</i>

75
00:08:03.954 --> 00:08:07.165
Uh. you know. taking it day by day.

76
00:08:08.375 --> 00:08:09.793
<i>We miss you.</i>

77
00:08:11.169 --> 00:08:12.378
I wanna come home.

78
00:08:12.379 --> 00:08:14.047
[ominous music playing]

79
00:08:14.881 --> 00:08:16.716
I know. bud. You will.

80
00:08:17.425 --> 00:08:18.426
<i>Soon.</i>

81
00:08:21.096 --> 00:08:23.265
<i>Just hang in there a little while longer.</i>

82
00:08:23.849 --> 00:08:25.809
Then we'll all be home together.

83
00:08:28.520 --> 00:08:30.939
Hey. Group's starting.

84
00:08:32.816 --> 00:08:34.693
- I gotta go.
- <i>Zack...</i>

85
00:08:51.334 --> 00:08:52.711
[inmate 1] Give me your biscuit.

86
00:08:55.672 --> 00:08:57.757
- What?
- You ain't gonna eat it.

87
00:08:58.592 --> 00:08:59.676
Give it to me.

88
00:09:01.762 --> 00:09:02.763
I might.

89
00:09:03.263 --> 00:09:04.264
[inmate 1] Really?

90
00:09:07.476 --> 00:09:09.144
I think you're too afraid to eat.

91
00:09:10.520 --> 00:09:12.605
Everyone in here knows
that she's gonna fuck you up.

92
00:09:12.606 --> 00:09:14.231
[ominous music playing]

93
00:09:14.232 --> 00:09:15.484
But she's making you wait

94
00:09:16.067 --> 00:09:20.280
so that me and everyone in here
can get a piece of you first.

95
00:09:21.448 --> 00:09:23.241
Now give me the fucking biscuit.

96
00:09:28.580 --> 00:09:29.581
Fuck you.

97
00:09:30.081 --> 00:09:32.666
- [sinister. tense music playing]
- [both grunting]

98
00:09:32.667 --> 00:09:35.169
- [inmate 2] Holy fuck.
- [inmate 3] Get her bitch ass!

99
00:09:35.170 --> 00:09:37.630
[inmate 4 shouting indistinctly]

100
00:09:37.631 --> 00:09:39.466
[inmate 5] Little white girl!

101
00:09:41.301 --> 00:09:43.302
- [Nevaeh shrieks]
- [inmates groan]

102
00:09:43.303 --> 00:09:45.555
[panting]

103
00:09:47.474 --> 00:09:50.351
- [grunting. whimpering]
- [inmate 6] Oh. shit!

104
00:09:50.352 --> 00:09:51.602
- [door lock buzzes]
- She's mine.

105
00:09:51.603 --> 00:09:53.312
[officer] Shit! Shut up.

106
00:09:53.313 --> 00:09:55.147
Goddamn it.

107
00:09:55.148 --> 00:09:56.565
Get down. All right.

108
00:09:56.566 --> 00:09:58.692
[chuckles]

109
00:09:58.693 --> 00:10:01.446
[breathing shakily]

110
00:10:20.090 --> 00:10:22.926
Shit. [breathing shakily]

111
00:10:32.769 --> 00:10:36.440
- [breathing heavily] Hey.
- [recording tone plays]

112
00:10:37.649 --> 00:10:39.108
Um. Noa. I'm fine.

113
00:10:39.109 --> 00:10:42.903
[stammers] I'm. um...
Look. I know this sounds insane.

114
00:10:42.904 --> 00:10:44.780
- but I'm with Crystal Cady...
- [shuffling]

115
00:10:44.781 --> 00:10:47.367
...and I need you to dig up
everything you can on her.

116
00:10:48.243 --> 00:10:49.327
I'll do the same.

117
00:10:50.829 --> 00:10:54.832
Will you tell Tom
that I'm gonna make this right?

118
00:10:54.833 --> 00:10:57.252
- Okay? [breathing heavily]
- [message sent tone plays]

119
00:11:08.138 --> 00:11:11.683
- [glass clinking]
- [breathing shakily]

120
00:11:13.852 --> 00:11:15.896
Okay. [inhales sharply]

121
00:11:16.730 --> 00:11:18.064
[breathing shakily]

122
00:11:33.997 --> 00:11:36.291
[Crystal] Well. good morning. princess.

123
00:11:39.669 --> 00:11:40.753
Morning.

124
00:11:40.754 --> 00:11:44.299
I hope my humble abode
was up to your standards.

125
00:11:45.091 --> 00:11:46.218
I survived.

126
00:11:48.762 --> 00:11:49.763
You want a beer?

127
00:11:52.724 --> 00:11:53.850
Thanks.

128
00:11:57.771 --> 00:11:58.772
[Crystal chuckles]

129
00:11:59.689 --> 00:12:02.901
What. did you learn that
from your sorority sisters?

130
00:12:06.530 --> 00:12:10.367
Well. who's to say they taught me?
Maybe I taught them.

131
00:12:13.578 --> 00:12:16.539
Maybe I taught their boyfriends
and boyfriends taught them.

132
00:12:16.540 --> 00:12:18.625
- You're mouthy.
- Mmm.

133
00:12:20.752 --> 00:12:21.920
Where's my gun?

134
00:12:23.588 --> 00:12:24.965
Safekeeping.

135
00:12:29.469 --> 00:12:30.470
So...

136
00:12:32.013 --> 00:12:33.682
tell me about you and Max.

137
00:12:37.978 --> 00:12:38.979
You first.

138
00:12:39.563 --> 00:12:42.107
[ominous music playing]

139
00:12:42.774 --> 00:12:45.277
[officer] Bowden. you got a visitor.

140
00:12:56.079 --> 00:12:57.539
[breathes shakily]

141
00:13:12.345 --> 00:13:16.348
Wow. It's very impressive.
the way you look.

142
00:13:16.349 --> 00:13:17.350
[chuckles]

143
00:13:17.893 --> 00:13:20.436
Hey. are you making any friends here?

144
00:13:20.437 --> 00:13:21.896
I worry about you.

145
00:13:21.897 --> 00:13:25.691
How do your... your fellow inmates
feel about prosecutors?

146
00:13:25.692 --> 00:13:28.527
They're... They're tricky with that. no?

147
00:13:28.528 --> 00:13:29.779
They don't know yet?

148
00:13:29.780 --> 00:13:31.155
Wow. They don't know yet.

149
00:13:31.156 --> 00:13:34.116
Well. it won't be long
until they find out.

150
00:13:34.117 --> 00:13:36.118
Are you just here
to run your fucking mouth. man.

151
00:13:36.119 --> 00:13:39.830
or do you have anything worthwhile
to say to me?

152
00:13:39.831 --> 00:13:40.915
Yes. actually.

153
00:13:40.916 --> 00:13:43.209
Well. I want to tell you something
that is very important.

154
00:13:43.210 --> 00:13:48.547
Make sure you save
all the Kikkoman soy sauce packages

155
00:13:48.548 --> 00:13:50.299
- from the commissary.
- [laughing]

156
00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:53.093
Because then you mix
the soy sauce with the mayo

157
00:13:53.094 --> 00:13:54.595
and you can create this sauce

158
00:13:54.596 --> 00:13:57.431
- that'll really fix the most bland meal.
- Fuck you.

159
00:13:57.432 --> 00:13:58.933
- [knocks on glass]
- Hey!

160
00:13:58.934 --> 00:14:01.602
[laughing] It's true though.

161
00:14:01.603 --> 00:14:02.604
Sorry. sorry.

162
00:14:03.188 --> 00:14:05.398
You're gonna wanna hear this.

163
00:14:12.614 --> 00:14:14.907
[blows] How does it feel?

164
00:14:14.908 --> 00:14:16.535
How does it feel. Tom?

165
00:14:17.953 --> 00:14:18.954
Being in there.

166
00:14:21.039 --> 00:14:26.127
You need permission
to go and eat or sleep or take a shit.

167
00:14:26.128 --> 00:14:27.962
You need permission for everything.

168
00:14:27.963 --> 00:14:29.463
[sinister music playing]

169
00:14:29.464 --> 00:14:35.511
How are you feeling
with the experience of losing. totally.

170
00:14:35.512 --> 00:14:39.390
the control and the will
of doing what you want when you need?

171
00:14:39.391 --> 00:14:41.226
You don't have that in there. right?

172
00:14:42.102 --> 00:14:43.103
It's hard.

173
00:14:45.105 --> 00:14:51.153
But I'm giving you the possibility
to become the man your family needs.

174
00:14:51.778 --> 00:14:57.199
One of my friends is going to send you
a gift to your cell. Today.

175
00:14:57.200 --> 00:14:58.869
So... [inhales deeply]

176
00:15:00.162 --> 00:15:01.412
...a gift.

177
00:15:01.413 --> 00:15:02.414
In your cell.

178
00:15:04.499 --> 00:15:05.917
It will be your salvation.

179
00:15:17.053 --> 00:15:19.514
[Crystal] Sounds like
he did a real number on you.

180
00:15:21.183 --> 00:15:23.727
Fucked up your whole life.

181
00:15:24.311 --> 00:15:25.854
Fucked up your family.

182
00:15:26.897 --> 00:15:27.939
That's Max.

183
00:15:29.399 --> 00:15:30.734
That's gotta sting.

184
00:15:31.693 --> 00:15:35.489
but I guess you were really into him. huh?

185
00:15:37.199 --> 00:15:39.033
No. No. course not.

186
00:15:39.034 --> 00:15:40.743
I told you. what you saw...

187
00:15:40.744 --> 00:15:41.911
He kissed me...

188
00:15:41.912 --> 00:15:43.287
Against your will.

189
00:15:43.288 --> 00:15:44.456
Yes. against my will.

190
00:15:45.040 --> 00:15:47.167
[chuckling] But you sure looked willing.

191
00:15:47.959 --> 00:15:49.252
What about you?

192
00:15:49.836 --> 00:15:53.673
Why are you following him around?
Stalking him. taking pictures.

193
00:15:54.257 --> 00:15:56.426
Seems to me
like you're the one infatuated.

194
00:15:57.177 --> 00:15:59.553
- Oh. I'm not infatuated.
- Mmm.

195
00:15:59.554 --> 00:16:01.931
It's because I know Max Cady

196
00:16:01.932 --> 00:16:04.141
and I know what he's up to.

197
00:16:04.142 --> 00:16:05.726
That's why I have those pictures.

198
00:16:05.727 --> 00:16:09.855
because as long as he knows that
I have pictures of him doing bad stuff.

199
00:16:09.856 --> 00:16:11.441
then he won't come after me.

200
00:16:11.942 --> 00:16:15.028
And no. you cannot see them
because they're mine.

201
00:16:17.072 --> 00:16:18.073
What about Amy?

202
00:16:19.407 --> 00:16:20.408
And Melissa?

203
00:16:21.284 --> 00:16:22.576
What did he do to them?

204
00:16:22.577 --> 00:16:27.541
I'm just saying that when Max
wants to make something happen.

205
00:16:28.250 --> 00:16:29.626
he just makes it happen.

206
00:16:30.585 --> 00:16:32.963
He'll make people do anything he wants.

207
00:16:34.089 --> 00:16:35.090
Anything. like...

208
00:16:36.675 --> 00:16:37.968
kill themselves?

209
00:16:39.469 --> 00:16:42.180
Amy Brancato. she had moved to Asheville.

210
00:16:42.681 --> 00:16:43.973
She got a new man.

211
00:16:43.974 --> 00:16:46.100
she was getting her life back together

212
00:16:46.101 --> 00:16:48.936
and then Max comes calling
and that's all it took.

213
00:16:48.937 --> 00:16:52.273
She came here and she started
living with her stepmom again.

214
00:16:52.274 --> 00:16:54.609
And that's where she was
when they found her.

215
00:16:57.320 --> 00:16:58.447
What else do you know?

216
00:17:05.996 --> 00:17:06.997
[sniffs]

217
00:17:30.479 --> 00:17:33.440
[line ringing]

218
00:17:34.149 --> 00:17:35.150
Hey.

219
00:17:36.067 --> 00:17:37.486
[Nevaeh] <i>I gave her a taste.</i>

220
00:17:38.612 --> 00:17:40.404
<i>She knows I'm gonna make her life hell.</i>

221
00:17:40.405 --> 00:17:42.072
I'm so lucky to have you.

222
00:17:42.073 --> 00:17:43.784
[chuckles] My little girl.

223
00:17:45.535 --> 00:17:46.953
I could help more. you know.

224
00:17:48.079 --> 00:17:50.540
Um. if I was with you.

225
00:17:51.458 --> 00:17:53.542
<i>Have you figured out how to get me out?</i>

226
00:17:53.543 --> 00:17:56.504
Nevaeh. you are my eyes and my ears.
and I need you.

227
00:17:56.505 --> 00:17:58.798
- I can't get you out yet.
- [unsettling music playing]

228
00:17:58.799 --> 00:18:01.133
- You said it would be soon.
- <i>And it will be.</i>

229
00:18:01.134 --> 00:18:03.511
<i>I just need one more thing.</i>

230
00:18:03.512 --> 00:18:09.017
I need you to find out
from Natalie where her mother is.

231
00:18:10.477 --> 00:18:11.686
<i>Can you do that for me?</i>

232
00:18:12.646 --> 00:18:13.729
Yeah.

233
00:18:13.730 --> 00:18:14.814
<i>Good.</i>

234
00:18:14.815 --> 00:18:15.816
Great.

235
00:18:17.067 --> 00:18:18.068
And then...

236
00:18:19.277 --> 00:18:20.403
[whispers] ...finish it.

237
00:18:21.988 --> 00:18:23.448
Like. kill Natalie?

238
00:18:25.325 --> 00:18:26.408
Like. for sure?

239
00:18:26.409 --> 00:18:28.120
Before Anna dies.

240
00:18:28.912 --> 00:18:31.248
I need her to feel the pain of...

241
00:18:32.916 --> 00:18:33.917
losing a child.

242
00:18:35.794 --> 00:18:36.795
Just like I did.

243
00:18:38.255 --> 00:18:39.589
I need her to feel that.

244
00:18:40.632 --> 00:18:42.050
<i>Think of what she did to me.</i>

245
00:18:42.717 --> 00:18:43.969
of what she did to you.

246
00:18:44.719 --> 00:18:47.138
Sixteen years we could have been together.

247
00:18:47.139 --> 00:18:48.140
Father and daughter.

248
00:18:49.057 --> 00:18:50.724
<i>Can you do that for me?</i>

249
00:18:50.725 --> 00:18:53.477
<i>And I'll be so proud of you.</i>

250
00:18:53.478 --> 00:18:54.937
And then you'll get me out...

251
00:18:54.938 --> 00:18:56.940
[breathing shakily] ...right?

252
00:19:00.694 --> 00:19:02.403
Right? [panting]

253
00:19:02.404 --> 00:19:03.487
Dad?

254
00:19:03.488 --> 00:19:05.615
<i>Daddy?</i> [panting continues]

255
00:19:08.368 --> 00:19:09.535
Yes.

256
00:19:09.536 --> 00:19:11.872
I love you so much.

257
00:19:12.456 --> 00:19:15.249
<i>Bye. I love you.</i>

258
00:19:15.250 --> 00:19:16.418
Bye.

259
00:19:16.918 --> 00:19:19.212
[breathing heavily]

260
00:19:23.425 --> 00:19:25.927
[ominous music playing]

261
00:19:35.896 --> 00:19:37.730
Why'd you stop that girl
from attacking me?

262
00:19:37.731 --> 00:19:41.942
Same reason I save tuna pouches
from commissary. To eat later.

263
00:19:41.943 --> 00:19:42.944
Don't do that.

264
